Tyrosine kinase</td><td valign="top" align="center" rowspan="1" colspan="1">2.56</td></tr><tr><td valign="top" align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">10</td><td valign="top" align="center" rowspan="1" colspan="1">DR0126</td><td valign="top" align="center" rowspan="1" colspan="1">312</td><td valign="top" align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">Chaperone protein DnaJ</td><td valign="top" align="center" rowspan="1" colspan="1">3.39</td></tr></tbody></table></table-wrap><p>The transcriptome of the R1&#x00394;dr1790 mutant was analyzed and compared with that of
the wild type strain under normal growth conditions using oligonucleotide
microarray to examine the expression of the entire gene repertoire of <italic>D.
radiodurans</italic> in response to <italic>dr1790</italic> knockout. In the
